## E. Executive Justification

### Presented to CFO / Audit Committee

**Problem Statement:**
Our aerospace division has entered a fixed-price, EUR 20M contract with an implied USD receivable of ~$21.87M (at current forward rates). Without hedging, FX movements of just ±5% create $2.19M swing in realized revenue—material enough to move earnings per share by several cents.

**Hedging Mandate:**
Treasury policy requires protection of receivables >$10M when FX volatility exceeds 10% annualized (current implied vol ~12%). This exposure qualifies.

**Decision Framework:**
| Criterion | Weight | Forward | MMH | Put | Collar | Unhedged |
|-----------|--------|---------|-----|-----|--------|----------|
| Downside Protection | 30% | ✓ | ✓ | ✓ | ✓ | ✗ |
| Upside Optionality | 25% | ✗ | ✗ | ✓✓ | ◐ | ✓✓ |
| Cost Efficiency | 20% | ✓ | ◐ | ◐ | ✓✓ | N/A |
| Audit / Compliance | 15% | ✓ | ◐ | ✓ | ◐ | ✓ |
| Treasury Flexibility | 10% | ✗ | ◐ | ✓ | ◐ | ✓ |
| **Weighted Score** | | 72% | 65% | **88%** | 74% | 60% |

**Put Strategy Advantage:**
- Achieves 88% score by balancing protection (scored highly on downside control) with optionality (scored highly on upside capture)
- Premium cost of $380K (1.74%) is **offset by optionality value** estimated at $450K–$550K (Black-Scholes, implied vol 12%)
- Treasury effectively purchases insurance (downside floor) at below intrinsic value

**Financial Impact:**
- **Base Case (S_T = F₀ = 1.0935):** Proceeds = $21.49M (after premium) vs. $21.87M unhedged
  - "Cost" appears to be $380K, but this is **insurance premium**, not pure cost
- **Upside Case (S_T = 1.15, +5%):** Proceeds = $22.62M vs. $23M unhedged
  - Opportunity cost only $380K (insurance premium)
- **Downside Case (S_T = 0.95, -13%):** Proceeds = $21.49M vs. $19M unhedged
  - **Protection value = $2.49M** ✓ Justifies premium and more

**Recommendation:**
Implement protective put hedge, purchasing EUR put option (K_PUT ≈ 1.0935, 12-month maturity) at $0.019/EUR. Execute within 5 trading days to lock volatility at current implied levels (12% annualized).

